      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LA BELLA ROSA (10) is yet to fill a placing in five starts but the last three have been decent efforts at the provincials. Steps out beyond 1400m for the first time which looks a good move as she finds the line well. In the right race to finally get some runs on the board. PEAR BELLINI (7) has been in the money seven times from 13 runs and almost added an eighth last time out when a close fourth over 1400m at Taree. Goes well for M Bennett who is back aboard. Draws the fence and should run her usual honest race. EASY TRAPEZEE (2) has been freshened up since a modest effort over 1420m at Grafton a month ago. Lightly raced and not out of the contest. OUR PAPPY (1) has been showing tremendous pace before capitulating in shorter races of late. Interesting move to stretch to today's journey. Will give backers a sight. AELFWYNN (8) has been plain of late but might appreciate the blinkers going on.",
